{"pageHTML":["","<p><span style=\"color: rgb(218, 221, 241); font-size: 3.2vmin;\"><strong>The Tortoise and the Hare</strong></span></p><hr><p><span style=\"color: rgb(218, 221, 241);\"><strong>Once upon a time in a sunny forest, there lived a speedy hare and a slow but steady tortoise. <br><br>The hare loved to brag. “I’m the fastest animal in the forest!” he would say, hopping around. “No one can beat me in a race!”<br><br>The tortoise, who didn’t like showing off, calmly replied, “Maybe I’m slow, but I’d still like to race you.”<br><br>The hare burst out laughing. “You? Race me? This will be the easiest win of my life!”<br><br>All the animals gathered to watch. “Ready, set, go!” called the fox, and the race began.<br><br>The hare zoomed ahead so fast, he was out of sight in seconds. The tortoise moved slowly, step by step, with his short legs and heavy shell.<br><br>The hare reached a shady tree and looked back. He didn’t see the tortoise anywhere.<br><br>“This is too easy,” said the hare. “I’ll take a little nap. He’ll never catch up anyway.”<br><br>So the hare curled up under the tree and quickly fell asleep.<br><br>Meanwhile, the tortoise kept going—slow and steady. He didn’t stop to rest. He didn’t stop to snack. He just kept moving, one small step at a time.<br><br>After a while, the hare woke up and stretched. “Time to finish the race,” he said.<br><br>But when he looked down the path—he couldn’t believe his eyes!<br><br>The tortoise was almost at the finish line!<br><br>The hare ran as fast as he could, his feet thumping the ground, but it was too late.<br><br>The tortoise crossed the finish line first!<br><br>All the animals cheered. The hare looked surprised—and a little embarrassed.<br><br>The tortoise smiled kindly and said, “Slow and steady wins the race.”<br><br>From that day on, the hare learned not to brag, and he always remembered the lesson from his slow and steady friend.<br><br></strong></span></p>"],"storyData":{"dynamicBgList":[{"type":"color